annotation.TEXT: I guess this means that when Random picked the Old Man that one time earlier, it wasn't nearly as unlikely as it initially seemed, because I used the jump button to pick Random back then.
Oh, I hope the level ends soon! And I'm not going to use Infinite Time to get out of this one!
I wonder if things would've been way different had the game given me the Wave Beam instead of the Ice Beam on my previous life...
Oh, I found a hidden block. This is why I like to just fire randomly in the air, because I have no idea where most secrets are in Special.
Sorry, but I gotta change what the interface looks like here, as I can barely see my score and stuff up there.
To be continued...
Too bad I can't freeze Fire Bars.
I could've used that star a few seconds ago, but I guess I'll take it now.
Nuts. Doesn't look like Shadow can get those two coins. Only a short character like Link, Sophia III, or a plumber lacking in power ups can get them.
Hello, and welcome back to more SMB Crossover! Now, it's time to take on world 8 of the Special levels, but who shall I use?
Ow! And now I can't even freeze them!
I guess the Ninjis are Fighter Flies and the Lil Sparkies are Sidesteppers.
Argh! I can't believe I let myself get hit there, and I've lost some of my upgrades. However, I still have arrows!
I'm suspicious of the possibility of other hidden secrets, but I don't want to waste too much time searching for them...
Hmm... Well, freezing enemies might come in handy in this level.
So, we've got castle walls in the background, just like in 8-3 of the original SMB. Also, Hammer Bros., just like in SMB's 8-3 as well.

...Wait a minute... I still have the Varia Suit, right? This is perfect, as I finally get to show you guys a character's Fire Bar immunity! (Seeing how Fire Man got gypped when it turned out that the 4-4 castle had no Fire Bars...)
Alright, now for 8-3, let's go with the one vote that wasn't intended specifically for 8-4...
Oh, multi-coin block! And... Oh, I'm running out of time, yet again!
Oh, good. We're in a less wet area now. But what's not so good are these DK enemies here...

Well, Random got 2 votes, so I guess I'll start with Random. Also, there were votes were for Mario, Zero Suit Samus, and Dr. Wily (Bass) to be used in 8-4. And, the other vote was for Bartz (Link), which didn't specify a level.
I don't have my Varia anymore, so I must be sure to avoid these Fire Bars.
Okay, it doesn't look like there was anything else hidden near that block.
Alright, now for 8-2, I believe I'll go with Random again, since all but one of the other votes were meant for 8-4.
At least Shadow has a good melee attack.
Whoa, time limit! Alright, nuts to those losers! I'm outta here!
And that would be the clock! So, I have a bit more time to live!
Oh, yes! Gotta love that Final Fantasy Adventure music!
Umm... But, if I did need the item, how would I reach it? Shouldn't this have been one space lower for characters that can't jump five spaces high?
Speaking of flames, here's more Fire Bars, which are far more predictable.
Another random, mostly pointless hidden coin block that I don't have time to waste on?
Alright, landed the 5000 and the 6!
Alright, there we go.
Whoa, big Fire Bar.

Whoa, careful of that Fighter Fly. I hate how I have to hit enemies twice as much to kill them when I have the Ice Beam, and I can't blame SMB Crossover for this, because that's how it worked in the original Metroid too.

Now, those last three levels took me a while, and I could try to squeeze 8-4 into this video, but I have no idea how long 8-4 will take me, and I just don't feel like doing it right now, so I'll be saving 8-4 for next time!
Now, if you pick Random with the jump button, it'll choose someone randomly, but with the same skin that was previously used with that character, like this.
I'm kind of low on NP, so I'm going to have to get in melee range to deal with any more Hammer Bros.
Oh, yeah. One thing I noticed about picking Random now, if you do so with the special button, like this...
D'oh! Too early...
Aww... The Ice Beam again? I wanted the Wave Beam.
...Bartz from Final Fantasy V!
Well, let's try this again and do it faster this time. And unfortunately, since I'm in world 8, I have to start the level from the beginning, right?
Whoa, Magikoopas have taken the Hammer Brothers' place!

KA-BOOOOM!!! Well, that sucked. Also, I noticed that I went kablooey the instant the timer hit 0, instead of 1 game second later, which is technically an inaccuracy, as you do get one more tick at 0 before dying to the timer in the original SMB.
Umm... What the heck? This castle looks weird...
Come on, somebody give me missiles...
How come my sword beams seem to be dealing less damage than a direct hit with the sword itself? In the original Zelda, the sword beams were equal in power to the sword itself.
Wait, isn't there a clock hidden somewhere in this level?
Ooh, found a hidden power up block, which contains an item I don't need.
LOL, whatever.
Oh, no... I can handle jumping over barrels, if there's only barrels... But add a flame into the mix and that spells trouble!
Whoa, stay away from me, Blooper!
Votes for Google to change the comments back: At least 230,569.
So, place your votes for who you want me to finish the game with! It could be Mario, Zero Suit Samus, Dr. Wily, or anyone else!
Yep, no checkpoints for me, unless maybe I turned on the Extra Checkpoints cheat, but I'm not gonna do that.
I'll take that power up, thank you very much.

Well, there's my answer, maybe. There was a hidden 1-up in the top door of the castle, which I happened to hit with a shuriken. Still, I don't think that was what the hidden coin block was meant for, but whatever.
And I'm running out of time again! I hope I'm getting close to the goal!
Oh, is this the goal? Yes!

ARGH!!! Man, Ryu has had nothing but bad luck when it comes to those flames, and this is only the second time I've encountered them in the game! Was there a hidden hammer nearby that I wasn't aware of? Let me know if there was.
Definitely appropriate "Hurry up!" music, by the way!
Umm... But that's it? Just a seemingly random hidden coin block here and nothing else?
I believe this music is from the corridor right before the Metroid Queen in Metroid II. (And the star music, before it was interrupted by the time warning, was from the ending of Metroid II.)
Aw, what? An underwater level now? I guess I could try climbing up and go over the roof here, but I'm not actually gonna do that.
Alright, so can Samus avoid having any bad luck here today? We'll find out eventually...
Whoa, what the?! That was weird! How come I clipped through the top of the pipe there?
Yes, one last 6 FTW!
So, was the hidden coin block on the left used for anything besides reaching the single coin above it?
In this case, I got Ryu's Shadow skin, yet again.
I don't think I'm gonna make it... NOOOOO!!!!!

Oh, I don't believe I found this hidden block last time. Umm... I hope there was nothing valuable hidden just above it, as I can't jump that high. (Well, I could've bomb jumped, but that would've been time-consuming.)
Demo count: 10
No "Toasty" here!
Whoa! For a split-second there, I thought I wouldn't make that jump!
...It'll pick a random skin of the random character it chose. In this case, I got one of the regular Samus skins. However, if you pick Random with the jump button... Well, I'll get to that later.
Obviously, I like breaking loads of bricks. Too bad I don't have an AWESOME SPREAD GUN to help me with this. (Even if I picked Bill for this level, he's got the fire gun right now.)
Huh. Well, whatever. I'm wasting time, so let's move on here.
Okay, that one's good. Yeah, certain backgrounds and interface skins just don't mix well.
Umm... That's probably the ending staircase, so I'm debating whether or not to quickly check those remaining bricks... No, forget them. If they held anything good, let me know!
I mean, some other five-tile high things were lowered by one space for the weaker jumpers, such as the first row of bricks with a power up in them at the beginning of 7-1 in the original SMB levels.
Okay, they're gone, but so are 10 of my arrows, and my blue and red rings, and my magical boomerang...
Oh, come on! The major problem with the flame is how randomly it moves, and the barrels just compound the issue.

Oh, whoops. I think we've already seen the Ice Beam explanation, but I guess I didn't ever pick up the Ice Beam (and thus trigger this tutorial message) when replaying the levels after the previous version update.
Let's go over the top this time, just to break some more bricks.
Alright, an underground level with some icicles. I'd much rather deal with icicles than flames!
Why am I wasting time with these losers? I should just freeze them and run past!
Oh, awesome! Shadow didn't get fried that time!
